ARMY V NAVY DRUNKEN ANTICS CANNOT BE REPEATED
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Richmond Council has expressed severe concern regarding the
    behaviour of fans attending the Army and Navy match at the RFU
    Stadium last Saturday.

    It follows many reports over the long weekend from residents
    expressing outrage at witnessing scenes of drunken behaviour,
    urination in gardens, fans passed out in the streets, attempted
    theft and, in one instance, a woman being hospitalised after being
    struck by a bottle thrown by fans in St Margarets.

