COUNCILS SEEKS HEATHROW APPEAL
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Following the High Court's decision on 1 May 2019 to dismiss the
    legal challenge brought by four London councils and others, expert
    legal opinion has been sought as to whether there are any grounds
    to appeal this decision.

    There is no automatic right of appeal and permission to appeal is
    needed, in the first instance, from the court which heard the
    original legal challenge.

