PLAN TO CONSERVE BOROUGH'S SPECIES AND HABITAT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    A Plan to conserve the borough's richly diverse plant and wildlife
    for future generations was launched yesterday at the London Wetland
    Centre in Barnes.

    Richmond Council Cabinet Member for Environment, Planning and
    Sustainability, Cllr Martin Elengorn joined Sir David Attenborough,
    members of the South West London Environment Network (SWLEN) and
    others to help launch the Richmond upon Thames' Biodiversity Action
    Plan on Thursday (9th May).

